track_notes: This track starts int he county park

This is the route I followed for a two-summit activation day of Hualapai Peak and Aspen Peak.  It was a beautiful day of hiking with awesome views and generally nice trails.  Hualapai Peak required a rock climb at the top which tested my abilities.  I left most of my gear including the gps at the clearing at the top of the road, and scrambled up the rocks until I was in the Activation Zone - I did not feel confident enough to go all the way up.  Next time I will look for a better route up.  I do not recommend activating this summit if you are nervous about exposed rock climbing.  Aspen Peak was better but the final ascent for this one was also a bit difficult, especially with tired legs, with some light rock climbing.  There is a nice meadow under the summit block which is in the Activation Zone.  Note that the road is an alternate route, I chose to use the trails for a little additional exploring.
track_title: Hualapai Peak and Aspen Peak - Two Summits
